Following prior work, standardized unexpected earnings (SUE) is defined as actual earnings per share from the I/B/E/S Detail file minus the average of all outstanding forecasts on the I/B/E/S Detail file (less than 90 days old) divided by the cross‐sectional standard deviation of the forecasts:

